(Non-VPS related offer approved by @mpkossen)

Hi everyone!

I would like to re-introduce you to MXroute, a company that revolves around the idea of managed e-mail hosting for people like you. Developers, admins, I'm talking to you. You don't need anything fancy, you just want e-mail hosting that works, that isn't parsed for advertisements, and that gives you reasonable package restrictions instead of annoying plans like "$X per user." You could do it yourself, but why? The complications can be overwhelming at times, and sometimes you'd rather be focusing on your other projects.

MXroute has been growing a lot, and the result has been a dramatic change in it's platform that ultimately provides a more stable environment. It is and will always be a work in progress, there are always improvements to be made. We recently switched our platform to cPanel, but I assure you that one cannot simply install cPanel on any old VPS and match the quality of our managed e-mail service (Customized configurations, powerful spam filtering, mail forwarding without being rate limited by Google every hour).

Here are some features:&lt;br&gt;
- Mail hosting for your domain&lt;br&gt;
- cPanel based control panel&lt;br&gt;
- DNS hosting&lt;br&gt;
- DKIM&lt;br&gt;
- OwnCloud&lt;br&gt;
- Roundcube and SquirrelMail

